WEBVTT

1
00:00:22.460 --> 00:00:25.420
We Don't Need the Memories

2
00:00:50.270 --> 00:00:52.760
Could the one to keep our eye on this match

3
00:00:52.760 --> 00:00:55.240
be the one people are calling the 
top high school setter,

4
00:00:55.240 --> 00:00:57.950
Inarizaki's Miya Atsumu?

5
00:00:57.950 --> 00:01:03.450
Indeed. But we should keep our 
eyes on Karasuno's setter, as well.

6
00:00:57.950 --> 00:01:03.450
Tsubakihara (Kanagawa)
Karasuno (Miyagi)
Inarizaki (Hyogo)

7
00:01:03.450 --> 00:01:06.410
Karasuno High School's Kageyama Tobio...

8
00:01:06.410 --> 00:01:10.460
He's another skilled player who was invited 
to the All-Japan Youth Camp this year.

9
00:01:10.460 --> 00:01:13.420
We're definitely seeing a setter battle 
between the East and the West!

10
00:01:17.320 --> 00:01:18.590
That jump was really good!

11
00:01:29.320 --> 00:01:31.070
I forgot to hit!

12
00:01:31.780 --> 00:01:34.920
How could I waste an opportunity like that?!

13
00:01:35.280 --> 00:01:37.540
You don't need to be that depressed about it.

14
00:01:39.240 --> 00:01:43.150
Isn't that the first time Hinata's been 
distracted by anything other than a toss

15
00:01:43.150 --> 00:01:44.710
that went up?

16
00:01:48.560 --> 00:01:52.320
If you ever do that again during a match,
 I'm never setting to you again.

17
00:01:52.320 --> 00:01:54.710
You need to make sure you can do both.

18
00:01:55.280 --> 00:01:56.720
You absolutely suck!

19
00:01:56.720 --> 00:01:57.900
Got it!

20
00:02:03.880 --> 00:02:06.060
Did something click with him

21
00:02:07.780 --> 00:02:09.430
after he saw the real deal?

22
00:02:09.920 --> 00:02:10.840
But...

23
00:02:11.770 --> 00:02:14.200
Even if he's able to make 
that boom jump a success,

24
00:02:14.200 --> 00:02:18.940
I didn't expect Hinata's contact 
point to change that drastically.

25
00:02:19.460 --> 00:02:21.530
This is going to throw us off.

26
00:02:42.010 --> 00:02:49.020
Haikyu!!

27
00:03:59.210 --> 00:04:04.130
We Don't Need the Memories

28
00:03:59.710 --> 00:04:05.680
Episode 14: Rhythm

29
00:04:04.130 --> 00:04:08.900
I could care less if it's loud or quiet.

30
00:04:11.420 --> 00:04:12.710
That's place is hard to reach...

31
00:04:13.730 --> 00:04:16.590
And the receive is a bit sloppy. 
Tanaka goes in for the last shot!

32
00:04:14.360 --> 00:04:15.730
Got it! Tanaka-san!

33
00:04:17.700 --> 00:04:18.400
One touch!

34
00:04:18.400 --> 00:04:21.190
Free ball!

35
00:04:21.190 --> 00:04:22.540
Got it!

36
00:04:31.520 --> 00:04:34.670
Miya Atsumu sets the ball 
on the first touch!

37
00:04:34.670 --> 00:04:37.900
Then Ojiro Aran smashes it over the net!

38
00:04:38.910 --> 00:04:41.510
Karasuno High has completely 
stopped in their tracks!

39
00:04:42.090 --> 00:04:45.050
Aran

40
00:04:42.350 --> 00:04:45.050
Nice kill, Aran!

41
00:04:45.050 --> 00:04:48.060
Nice kill, Aran! Jump, jump, Aran!

42
00:04:45.050 --> 00:04:48.470
We Don't Need the Memories

43
00:04:48.060 --> 00:04:50.540
One more time!

44
00:04:48.820 --> 00:04:50.540
Nice kill!

45
00:04:50.540 --> 00:04:52.060
You scared the crap outta me!

46
00:04:53.760 --> 00:04:57.720
Inarizaki's always breaking the mold.

47
00:04:57.720 --> 00:05:01.280
The ultimate challengers...

48
00:05:01.720 --> 00:05:05.740
Aran's not bad, though I'm better!
 Right, Akaashi?

49
00:05:05.740 --> 00:05:06.500
Yes.

50
00:05:07.760 --> 00:05:10.120
Of course that was a very 
direct surprise attack,

51
00:05:10.520 --> 00:05:12.720
but they were also trying to say,

52
00:05:12.720 --> 00:05:16.640
"We're not going to be overwhelmed by our 
first match. This is a piece of cake,"

53
00:05:16.640 --> 00:05:18.960
and put pressure on them.

54
00:05:19.490 --> 00:05:25.110
I can keep calm while watching them play, 
but it'd suck playing against them.

55
00:05:26.560 --> 00:05:28.570
Wow, they piss me off.

56
00:05:33.100 --> 00:05:35.310
Nice serve!

57
00:05:39.190 --> 00:05:40.730
Right at the whistle?!

58
00:05:42.320 --> 00:05:43.440
Sorry! That was a bit long!

59
00:05:45.840 --> 00:05:47.640
He managed to rebound without turning around!

60
00:05:47.640 --> 00:05:48.490
That was good!

61
00:05:49.110 --> 00:05:50.200
There!

62
00:05:50.490 --> 00:05:53.160
We're up against the ultimate challengers.

63
00:05:53.640 --> 00:05:54.490
But...

64
00:05:59.650 --> 00:06:00.710
We're just as much the challengers

65
00:06:03.440 --> 00:06:05.610
when it comes to volleyball.

66
00:06:15.480 --> 00:06:18.860
Hinata Shoyo ran out and got the point!

67
00:06:19.310 --> 00:06:23.560
That's the Karasuno first-year 
duo's famous slide attack!

68
00:06:21.590 --> 00:06:22.620
All right!

69
00:06:23.560 --> 00:06:25.190
Yeah!

70
00:06:26.100 --> 00:06:28.150
Huh?

71
00:06:28.150 --> 00:06:30.410
Huh?!

72
00:06:30.860 --> 00:06:34.020
Way to go, Hinata!

73
00:06:34.020 --> 00:06:35.080
Absolutely terrifying.

74
00:06:35.590 --> 00:06:37.510
Their first attack is always a killer.

75
00:06:38.900 --> 00:06:42.090
Man, I almost ran into that 
guy with the scary face.

76
00:06:42.800 --> 00:06:45.960
I almost fell for Hinata's feint, too.

77
00:06:45.960 --> 00:06:47.290
Wow...

78
00:06:45.960 --> 00:06:49.430
Inarizaki                                                       Karasuno

79
00:06:47.290 --> 00:06:48.620
What the heck was that crazy shot?!

80
00:06:48.620 --> 00:06:49.430
It sure was crazy!

81
00:06:49.850 --> 00:06:53.550
That's called a slide. You don't 
see that much in boys' volleyball.

82
00:06:53.550 --> 00:06:54.680
Huh...

83
00:06:55.440 --> 00:06:58.460
So it's fast enough to break through a block...

84
00:06:58.460 --> 00:07:01.050
Yet they didn't sacrifice any height, either.

85
00:07:02.260 --> 00:07:04.570
How frickin' cool is that?!

86
00:07:04.940 --> 00:07:08.110
That thing's even cooler to see in person!

87
00:07:08.110 --> 00:07:08.830
What's your deal?

88
00:07:08.830 --> 00:07:12.160
You always mentally regress, like, 
five years when we're in a match.

89
00:07:12.160 --> 00:07:13.530
Shut yer trap!

90
00:07:13.530 --> 00:07:16.990
We Don't Need the Memories

91
00:07:19.960 --> 00:07:23.910
It doesn't really seem like we're 
applying pressure to them...

92
00:07:23.910 --> 00:07:27.680
That four-eyes earlier was 
basically smirkin' the whole time.

93
00:07:27.680 --> 00:07:30.820
I mean, you can try to distract 
my serve all you want, but...

94
00:07:31.760 --> 00:07:33.930
Should we switch things up early?

95
00:07:33.930 --> 00:07:35.850
Yeah.

96
00:07:35.850 --> 00:07:39.600
We Don't Need the Memories

97
00:07:38.550 --> 00:07:41.870
The whole team that placed 
second at the Inter-High

98
00:07:41.870 --> 00:07:43.880
is giving it their all to beat us!

99
00:07:45.640 --> 00:07:48.030
When it's my turn to serve...

100
00:07:49.490 --> 00:07:52.570
It'll be hundreds of them versus me!

101
00:08:05.540 --> 00:08:10.920
We Don't Need the Memories

102
00:08:12.000 --> 00:08:13.690
They're going faster and faster.

103
00:08:22.310 --> 00:08:24.310
That serve toss wasn't the best.

104
00:08:32.520 --> 00:08:34.280
His first step was perfect!

105
00:08:36.740 --> 00:08:38.700
They're going into a quick from there?!

106
00:08:40.160 --> 00:08:43.120
We Don't Need the Memories

107
00:08:40.160 --> 00:08:45.160
Nice kill, Ren! Jump, 
jump, Ren! One more time!

108
00:08:43.120 --> 00:08:45.470
Holy crap!

109
00:08:45.470 --> 00:08:47.310
You can tell with one look...

110
00:08:47.310 --> 00:08:49.230
His first step was as refined as it gets.

111
00:08:49.650 --> 00:08:51.800
That quick and accurate first step

112
00:08:52.120 --> 00:08:55.070
gives the setter time to set up and 
figure out where his teammates are,

113
00:08:55.070 --> 00:08:57.720
and gives them time to figure things out.

114
00:08:57.720 --> 00:09:01.930
When the middle blocker scores the point, 
the middle scores right back.

115
00:09:01.930 --> 00:09:05.100
Nice. Neither side is letting up.

116
00:09:15.400 --> 00:09:19.200
Are they going to use every last bit
 of the eight seconds they have?

117
00:09:28.130 --> 00:09:29.110
Nishinoya!

118
00:09:30.600 --> 00:09:31.800
I was a half-step late!

119
00:09:34.180 --> 00:09:35.470
Hell yeah!

120
00:09:35.860 --> 00:09:39.610
Nice, nice, Ryu! Push it, push it, Ryu!

121
00:09:39.610 --> 00:09:41.760
Cut them right off, Ina High!

122
00:09:42.180 --> 00:09:45.310
Hey, Ryu-chan's not half bad.

123
00:09:45.310 --> 00:09:49.680
Yeah. Their #10's feint was effective, too,

124
00:09:49.680 --> 00:09:53.860
but he's got a good eye on 
the blockers and the floor.

125
00:09:54.310 --> 00:09:57.950
He used to just smash the 
ball as hard as he could.

126
00:09:57.950 --> 00:09:59.900
S-Sure.

127
00:09:59.900 --> 00:10:02.220
She's staring way harder than I expected.

128
00:10:13.670 --> 00:10:14.790
It's like that one thing...

129
00:10:15.250 --> 00:10:19.430
Where people start syncing up their applause
 for, like, a long jump in track and field.

130
00:10:20.180 --> 00:10:22.400
But it's way different 
when you start it yourself

131
00:10:22.400 --> 00:10:24.890
than when people just 
randomly start it for you.

132
00:10:24.890 --> 00:10:29.370
Even if the crowd means well, it may just 
end up provoking Karasuno.

133
00:10:35.320 --> 00:10:36.030
Don't worry about it!

134
00:10:36.980 --> 00:10:38.060
That's not good.

135
00:10:38.060 --> 00:10:38.530
Huh?

136
00:10:39.010 --> 00:10:41.740
That rhythm that keeps getting faster.

137
00:10:41.740 --> 00:10:47.740
That pressure isn't obvious, but before 
you know it, they're setting the rhythm.

138
00:10:48.840 --> 00:10:51.150
I thought we'd just have 
to worry about the booing,

139
00:10:51.150 --> 00:10:53.400
but this is getting in the way, too.

140
00:10:53.810 --> 00:10:58.660
First, we gotta be on par with our serves,
 or we're not gonna get anywhere.

141
00:11:09.980 --> 00:11:11.440
Yeah!

142
00:11:11.440 --> 00:11:14.400
We Don't Need the Memories

143
00:11:11.440 --> 00:11:14.400
Nice serve, Aran!

144
00:11:14.400 --> 00:11:20.610
Inarizaki                                                                       Karasuno

145
00:11:14.720 --> 00:11:18.840
Inarizaki High's managed their second 
service ace already this match.

146
00:11:14.950 --> 00:11:16.490
Nice serve, Aran!

147
00:11:16.490 --> 00:11:19.900
Go, go, Aran! One more time!

148
00:11:18.840 --> 00:11:20.610
The difference in their 
scores just keeps growing.

149
00:11:33.800 --> 00:11:36.940
Inarizaki doesn't seem like 
they're established champions.

150
00:11:36.940 --> 00:11:41.130
They still have the feel of a team of 
upstarts that are climbing their way up.

151
00:11:41.130 --> 00:11:42.880
Then they've got their support...

152
00:11:43.410 --> 00:11:44.880
Inarizaki's cheering section

153
00:11:44.880 --> 00:11:47.790
seems more like cover fire 
than just your usual support.

154
00:11:47.790 --> 00:11:48.810
I see what you mean.

155
00:11:50.050 --> 00:11:51.810
Both on and off the court...

156
00:11:52.410 --> 00:11:54.020
They use sound and time

157
00:11:55.080 --> 00:11:57.960
to expand Inarizaki's territory.

158
00:12:04.100 --> 00:12:06.730
Well, their team's cheer 
squad is hella impressive!

159
00:12:07.700 --> 00:12:08.910
Karasuno

160
00:12:08.910 --> 00:12:10.120
Karasuno Taiko

161
00:12:13.570 --> 00:12:15.260
Sorry to keep you boys waiting!

162
00:12:16.960 --> 00:12:23.970
Haikyu!!

163
00:12:23.970 --> 00:12:30.970
Haikyu!!

164
00:12:30.970 --> 00:12:34.080
Nice serve, Aran!

165
00:12:33.480 --> 00:12:37.440
Inarizaki High's managed their second 
service ace already this match.

166
00:12:34.080 --> 00:12:39.400
Go, go, Aran! One more time!

167
00:12:37.440 --> 00:12:39.400
Inarizaki                                                                       Karasuno

168
00:12:37.440 --> 00:12:39.400
The difference in their 
scores just keeps growing.

169
00:12:41.360 --> 00:12:45.130
What the heck? Inarizaki's 
already taken over the arena.

170
00:12:45.980 --> 00:12:50.290
Atsumu... That first serve 
of yours was a bit off.

171
00:12:50.290 --> 00:12:53.400
Did you let the cheering squad distract you?

172
00:12:58.530 --> 00:13:01.840
If only you guys had beaten Nekoma,
 you'd be playing here, too, Suguru.

173
00:13:02.300 --> 00:13:07.090
Nohebi Academy Volleyball Team Former Captain
Daisho Suguru

174
00:13:02.680 --> 00:13:05.880
Y-Yup, Mika-chan.

175
00:13:13.770 --> 00:13:16.650
Wow, they're so cool!

176
00:13:16.650 --> 00:13:20.600
Talk about pressure... 
Glad I'm not playing against them.

177
00:13:22.780 --> 00:13:24.650
Karasuno Taiko

178
00:13:28.870 --> 00:13:30.190
Hey, Japanese taiko drums.

179
00:13:30.190 --> 00:13:31.330
That's awesome!

180
00:13:33.790 --> 00:13:36.250
Fly

181
00:13:37.140 --> 00:13:38.210
It's Saeko-neesan!

182
00:13:44.660 --> 00:13:46.400
Her awesomeness is lethal...

183
00:13:46.400 --> 00:13:48.180
That's definitely a new way to die.

184
00:13:48.740 --> 00:13:50.960
Thank goodness they made it in time.

185
00:13:50.960 --> 00:13:51.740
Yeah...

186
00:13:54.860 --> 00:13:56.060
You're late!

187
00:13:56.430 --> 00:13:59.580
My bad! We sorta got lost!

188
00:13:59.580 --> 00:14:02.300
I just figured you were 
drinking until morning again.

189
00:14:02.300 --> 00:14:05.610
I mean, I was drinking until 5 AM,
 but we still left on time.

190
00:14:07.030 --> 00:14:09.260
Nice serve!

191
00:14:15.250 --> 00:14:16.160
Yes!

192
00:14:16.160 --> 00:14:16.960
Thanks!

193
00:14:16.960 --> 00:14:19.560
Wow! He's so fast!

194
00:14:19.560 --> 00:14:21.420
The national tournament is scary!

195
00:14:21.790 --> 00:14:23.380
Nice serve, Hinata!

196
00:14:28.770 --> 00:14:31.610
It's always ideal to have it be 
silent when you're about to serve,

197
00:14:31.610 --> 00:14:34.570
but I really want to stop them 
from taking over the rhythm!

198
00:14:35.220 --> 00:14:38.270
It doesn't have to be loud 
enough to overpower them.

199
00:14:39.120 --> 00:14:41.580
As long as we can get a rhythm besides

200
00:14:41.580 --> 00:14:44.060
what Inarizaki is playing 
into the server's ears...

201
00:14:45.360 --> 00:14:46.400
Let's go!

202
00:14:50.660 --> 00:14:55.640
That one time really pissed me off.

203
00:14:59.840 --> 00:15:04.500
But our job here isn't to beat 
the opponent's cheer squad.

204
00:15:05.350 --> 00:15:09.150
We might not even be able to give 
our boys the push they need.

205
00:15:09.150 --> 00:15:11.720
Because they're gonna keep 
moving forward on their own.

206
00:15:12.480 --> 00:15:16.890
So we just need to regain the 
balance in here a bit.

207
00:15:24.900 --> 00:15:29.070
I suddenly feel like... 
I can hit the best serve ever!

208
00:15:29.600 --> 00:15:31.720
Despite all of Inarizuki's provocation...

209
00:15:31.720 --> 00:15:34.400
Karasuno's #10 isn't showing 
even a bit of panic.

210
00:15:34.400 --> 00:15:37.000
It almost looks like he's smiling a little.

211
00:15:37.540 --> 00:15:39.080
What kind of serve is he gonna do?

212
00:15:39.080 --> 00:15:41.660
A spike serve? A jump floater serve?

213
00:15:45.330 --> 00:15:46.420
Or a completely normal one.

214
00:15:46.420 --> 00:15:47.130
Aran!

215
00:15:47.130 --> 00:15:47.880
Got it!

216
00:15:49.960 --> 00:15:51.380
A double quick...

217
00:15:52.930 --> 00:15:54.720
A super quick one from the side...

218
00:15:54.720 --> 00:15:56.050
Tsukishima's gonna close in that cross.

219
00:16:11.590 --> 00:16:14.070
It hasn't touched the ground. It hit his foot.

220
00:16:14.440 --> 00:16:15.490
The hell?!

221
00:16:15.490 --> 00:16:17.180
Is that even allowed?

222
00:16:17.180 --> 00:16:20.000
According to the rules, yeah. It's just...

223
00:16:20.330 --> 00:16:22.000
Super embarrassing, probably.

224
00:16:22.000 --> 00:16:23.610
It's that guy again!

225
00:16:23.610 --> 00:16:25.000
Use your damn hands!

226
00:16:25.000 --> 00:16:27.000
I totally missed!

227
00:16:27.370 --> 00:16:29.670
Great job getting to the ball, Shoyo!

228
00:16:32.770 --> 00:16:34.570
I've gotta regain my dignity!

229
00:16:38.070 --> 00:16:39.540
Back tempo!

230
00:16:42.690 --> 00:16:43.770
Daichi-san!

231
00:16:45.480 --> 00:16:50.440
Fly

232
00:16:45.480 --> 00:16:51.290
Nice, nice, Daichi! Push it, 
push it, Daichi! One more time!

233
00:16:46.070 --> 00:16:47.480
Sawamura moves in from the right!

234
00:16:50.920 --> 00:16:52.390
Nice set!

235
00:16:52.390 --> 00:16:55.910
I totally yelled, "Back tempo!" in my head!

236
00:16:56.340 --> 00:16:59.910
I honestly thought the toss was going 
to Hinata Shoyo again!

237
00:17:00.480 --> 00:17:03.980
Maybe Inarizaki is watching
 Hinata-kun a little too closely.

238
00:17:03.980 --> 00:17:06.920
I can't say I blame them, though.

239
00:17:06.920 --> 00:17:10.300
Inarizaki                                                                       Karasuno

240
00:17:07.260 --> 00:17:10.300
Looks like Karasuno's getting 
back into a rhythm!

241
00:17:10.760 --> 00:17:15.510
I thought he was totally going 
for Hinata, but he stopped.

242
00:17:15.800 --> 00:17:18.090
He was trying to lure me in.

243
00:17:18.470 --> 00:17:22.010
It totally looked like he was 
setting to Hinata just now, huh?!

244
00:17:22.010 --> 00:17:23.930
Yes, it did.

245
00:17:24.790 --> 00:17:28.680
Simple decoys won't work on read blockers.

246
00:17:28.680 --> 00:17:32.520
But the first touch went up 
in the center of the court,

247
00:17:32.520 --> 00:17:36.230
and it looked like he was setting 
to Hinata, but it went further right.

248
00:17:36.660 --> 00:17:39.200
It's not just that Kageyama's got 
everything in his field of view.

249
00:17:39.200 --> 00:17:42.160
He probably knows how his 
opponents are viewing him.

250
00:17:42.160 --> 00:17:42.910
Also...

251
00:17:42.910 --> 00:17:46.920
Hinata's so tiny, but he sure 
makes himself known on the court!

252
00:17:49.060 --> 00:17:50.070
Indeed.

253
00:17:51.160 --> 00:17:54.940
Man... That totally looked 
like it was for me.

254
00:17:54.940 --> 00:17:57.090
You moron! Kageyama, you moron!

255
00:17:58.120 --> 00:18:00.560
Not only did they place second 
in the Inter-High,

256
00:18:00.560 --> 00:18:04.020
they also have that 
overpowering cheering squad.

257
00:18:04.020 --> 00:18:09.020
But we may have been overestimating 
them far more than necessary.

258
00:18:09.500 --> 00:18:11.980
It'll be okay. If we approach 
each problem one at a time,

259
00:18:11.980 --> 00:18:13.610
we'll be able to figure this out.

260
00:18:14.440 --> 00:18:15.100
Yes.

261
00:18:15.530 --> 00:18:18.450
Inarizaki                                                                                            Karasuno

262
00:18:15.530 --> 00:18:20.010
Nice kill, Hitoshi! Nice kill, Hitoshi!

263
00:18:18.450 --> 00:18:21.410
We Don't Need the Memories

264
00:18:20.010 --> 00:18:23.370
Jump, jump, Hitoshi! One more time!

265
00:18:26.330 --> 00:18:28.830
And there's the dual wielder again.

266
00:18:28.830 --> 00:18:31.550
What's that mean? Is he gonna use two balls?

267
00:18:31.550 --> 00:18:32.250
No!

268
00:18:33.080 --> 00:18:35.610
He can hit a spike serve
 or a jump float serve...

269
00:18:35.610 --> 00:18:40.140
Basically, they won't know if they're 
gonna get Azumane's serve, Kageyama's serve,

270
00:18:40.140 --> 00:18:42.680
or Tadashi's serve right up 
until he actually hits it.

271
00:18:42.680 --> 00:18:43.260
Ack!

272
00:18:43.970 --> 00:18:48.090
And depending on which one it is, 
the positioning for receiving will be different.

273
00:18:48.090 --> 00:18:50.170
If they're even a step off,

274
00:18:50.170 --> 00:18:54.700
that delay can prove fatal when 
the serve comes in at over 100 km/h.

275
00:18:57.110 --> 00:18:59.820
Miya Atsumu-kun is a dual wielder 
when it comes to serving.

276
00:18:59.820 --> 00:19:02.430
Does that mean we won't know

277
00:19:02.430 --> 00:19:04.990
which serve is coming until 
he actually tosses the ball?

278
00:19:04.990 --> 00:19:07.030
No, you can tell them apart.

279
00:19:08.770 --> 00:19:11.240
Count his steps. When he's serving,

280
00:19:11.240 --> 00:19:14.670
he routinely measures his distance 
by the number of footsteps.

281
00:19:14.670 --> 00:19:17.380
When he's going for a jump floater, 
he's four steps from the end line.

282
00:19:17.840 --> 00:19:20.130
When he's going to do 
a spike serve, it'll be six steps.

283
00:19:20.130 --> 00:19:22.630
That's how you'll be able to tell them apart.

284
00:19:23.730 --> 00:19:26.470
It'll make a huge difference if we 
can tell which one he's going for.

285
00:19:26.900 --> 00:19:31.440
They don't really show all the movements 
that go into doing a serve on TV, do they?

286
00:19:31.440 --> 00:19:33.330
I'm surprised you were able to figure that out!

287
00:19:33.330 --> 00:19:35.290
I did a lot of research!

288
00:19:35.290 --> 00:19:39.440
I looked at videos online and 
videos my buddies took, too.

289
00:19:39.970 --> 00:19:41.530
Thanks!

290
00:19:49.140 --> 00:19:50.160
That's four...

291
00:19:50.160 --> 00:19:51.500
A jump floater.

292
00:19:52.120 --> 00:19:54.520
Bring it!

293
00:19:56.120 --> 00:19:58.210
You may have figured that out...

294
00:20:00.570 --> 00:20:04.510
but that's just the starting line.

295
00:20:10.760 --> 00:20:12.090
It was only an instant!

296
00:20:12.090 --> 00:20:13.850
And it ended up in his face!

297
00:20:21.030 --> 00:20:23.960
Yet another service ace!

298
00:20:21.520 --> 00:20:27.300
Nice serve, Atsumu! Nice serve, Atsumu! 
Go, go, Atsumu! One more time!

299
00:20:23.960 --> 00:20:27.860
Miya Atsumu has two incredibly 
powerful serves under his belt!

300
00:20:29.670 --> 00:20:32.060
That was an excellent serve!

301
00:20:32.060 --> 00:20:35.580
Powerful serves can make
 the team powerful, too.

302
00:20:35.580 --> 00:20:39.290
If they don't cut this off soon, 
Karasuno is going to be in trouble.

303
00:20:36.880 --> 00:20:42.840
Inarizaki                                                            Karasuno

304
00:20:39.290 --> 00:20:41.310
Damn, that serve was insane!

305
00:20:41.310 --> 00:20:42.840
Wow...

306
00:20:44.160 --> 00:20:45.300
All right, guys.

307
00:20:45.770 --> 00:20:49.320
We've dealt with intense 
serves in the past, too.

308
00:20:49.720 --> 00:20:51.590
Now's not the time to panic.

309
00:20:52.260 --> 00:20:53.350
Right!

310
00:20:54.470 --> 00:20:56.330
Huh...

311
00:20:57.060 --> 00:21:04.780
Inarizaki High School

312
00:20:57.680 --> 00:20:59.080
Say, Samu.

313
00:20:59.560 --> 00:21:01.050
Yeah, Tsumu?

314
00:21:01.510 --> 00:21:04.780
We can't miss a chance 
to score. Am I right?

315
00:21:13.840 --> 00:21:15.160
Four steps.

316
00:21:15.640 --> 00:21:17.640
Another jump floater?

317
00:21:25.220 --> 00:21:26.180
Yes!

318
00:21:27.720 --> 00:21:28.850
Asahi-san!

319
00:21:30.480 --> 00:21:31.510
Got it!

320
00:21:35.300 --> 00:21:38.150
This position... This timing...

321
00:21:39.030 --> 00:21:40.360
This angle!

322
00:21:45.330 --> 00:21:47.380
It's perfection!

323
00:22:00.040 --> 00:22:02.750
We Don't Need the Memories

324
00:22:00.350 --> 00:22:02.750
Nice kill, Osamu!

325
00:22:03.290 --> 00:22:08.470
Nice kill, Osamu! Jump, 
jump, Osamu! One more time!

326
00:22:04.130 --> 00:22:06.970
The ball really did just show up.

327
00:22:06.970 --> 00:22:08.470
Hell yeah!

328
00:22:09.910 --> 00:22:12.350
Th-That was almost like...

329
00:22:12.730 --> 00:22:15.060
Hinata-kun and Kageyama-kun's

330
00:22:15.680 --> 00:22:17.430
weirdo quick?!

331
00:23:51.990 --> 00:23:56.990
Episode 15: Found

332
00:23:53.490 --> 00:23:54.990
Next time: "Found."
